  "text": "11 Sympathetic cooling relying on the Coulomb interaction between dissimilar ions is very efficient. For instance small ion crystals including molecular ions have been cooled to the motional ground state [CITATION_1] . Using an astute selective photo-ionization scheme combined with sympathetic cooling it has been possible to produce samples of rotationally and vibrationally state-selected, translationally cold molecular ions [CITATION_2] . We also note that alternative strategies are promising: the reader will find a recent review of sympathetic cooling of molecular ions by ultra-cold neutral atoms in [CITATION_3] .",
